# Endpoint credentials for OpenClaw. Provide ONE of the two keys below
# (or both — the OU LiteLLM Sandbox key is used first when both are set).
#
# Easiest path: set these as Codespaces secrets (the Codespace prompts you on
# creation). Then you can ignore this file.
#
# Otherwise, run `bash scripts/set-key.sh` and it will be written for you to
# ~/.openclaw/.env — do NOT commit your real key.

# FIRST CHOICE: OU LiteLLM Sandbox key (starts with sk-), issued by the course.
#LITELLM_API_KEY=sk-REPLACE_ME

# ALSO WORKS: your OWN OpenRouter key (starts with sk-or-). Create the account
# and key yourself at https://openrouter.ai (Settings → Keys), load ~$10 of
# credit, and set a credit limit on the key. Expect at most ~$10 of usage all
# term. Used automatically when no OU LiteLLM key is set.
#OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-REPLACE_ME
